lyrics:
[verse]
In a dim-lit café, composers convene
Whispering of melodies yet to be seen
Curiosity blooms, their minds intertwine
Seeking the new, a different artistic design

[chorus]
We're lost in this era, where old blends with new
Searching for inspiration, to conjure and brew
Notes on a canvas, harmonies we'll create
In this uncertain world, we'll elate and fascinate
